                    <comment id="12741866" author="tripod" created="Tue, 11 Aug 2009 14:40:09 +0100"  >the only workspace that is shared among all others is the version workspace and it is virtually mounted at /jcr:system/jcr:versionStorage. creating a new persistent workspace for just the activities is a bit overkill, also in the light of the upcoming restructure of the jcr:system shared space.&lt;br/&gt;
the problem is that a virtual item state provide can only have 1 root, so the activities were put below /jcr:system/jcr:versionStorage/jcr:activities.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
to change this we could:&lt;br/&gt;
1) try to allow multiple roots for virtual providers&lt;br/&gt;
2) introduce a activities workspace and create a virtual provider just for this&lt;br/&gt;
3) try to create a shared node at /jcr:system/jcr:activities&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
i favor to relax the spec in this respect, but will try if i can implement (1)</comment>
                    <comment id="12742314" author="tripod" created="Wed, 12 Aug 2009 13:19:43 +0100"  >found a way to expose the jcr:activities at the correct location.</comment>
